58
00:03:19.440 --> 00:03:21.560
Well, the first thing I do is

59
00:03:21.560 --> 00:03:24.035
I'm going to engage
an underwriter.

60
00:03:24.035 --> 00:03:26.120
Okay? An underwriter. Now,
an underwriter is going to

61
00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:28.490
be big investment bank.

62
00:03:28.490 --> 00:03:29.870
I think Goldman Sachs,

63
00:03:29.870 --> 00:03:31.550
that kind of bank.

64
00:03:31.550 --> 00:03:34.040
I'm going to have
probably little contest

65
00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:35.330
among investment banks.

66
00:03:35.330 --> 00:03:36.650
We call it a bake off.

67
00:03:36.650 --> 00:03:38.660
Right? Like someone's going

68
00:03:38.660 --> 00:03:40.430
to try to come up
with the best muffin.

69
00:03:40.430 --> 00:03:41.630
Right? That's what they did.

70
00:03:41.630 --> 00:03:45.890
They call it a bake off in
the investment banking world,

71
00:03:45.890 --> 00:03:48.410
where the different banks
come to me and

72
00:03:48.410 --> 00:03:51.200
pitch to me how they're going
to take my company public.

73
00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:52.550
How they think about my company,

74
00:03:52.550 --> 00:03:55.895
think about the
valuation and so on.

75
00:03:55.895 --> 00:03:57.410
They pitch to me.

76
00:03:57.410 --> 00:03:59.765
I pick one of them
and say, "Okay.

77
00:03:59.765 --> 00:04:01.430
It's going to be you and me.

78
00:04:01.430 --> 00:04:03.860
We're going to take
my company public. "

79
00:04:03.860 --> 00:04:06.695
Notice by the way here
that so now I'm engaging

80
00:04:06.695 --> 00:04:11.565
a bank that goes to
the market all the time.

81
00:04:11.565 --> 00:04:13.140
Right? If I engage Goldman.

82
00:04:13.140 --> 00:04:15.450
Well, Goldman Sachs
does a lot of IPOs.

83
00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:17.975
They've been doing IPOs all year.

84
00:04:17.975 --> 00:04:20.360
They've got a reputation

85
00:04:20.360 --> 00:04:22.970
with the capital markets
that I don't.

86
00:04:22.970 --> 00:04:24.635
I'm just a start-up.

87
00:04:24.635 --> 00:04:28.224
They haven't yet
heard of me probably

88
00:04:28.224 --> 00:04:34.785
but they will and when
they hear about me,

89
00:04:34.785 --> 00:04:36.260
it's not just me, it's also

90
00:04:36.260 --> 00:04:39.710
Goldman Sachs or whoever
the bank is that I choose,

91
00:04:39.710 --> 00:04:46.730
are sticking their neck
out for my reputation.

92
00:04:46.730 --> 00:04:49.250
Right? So, we choose a bank with

93
00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:53.615
a long track record of doing
IPOs and then what happens?

94
00:04:53.615 --> 00:04:57.935
Okay. Now, we start the process
with the regulators.

95
00:04:57.935 --> 00:05:01.730
Okay? So now, together
with the investment bank,

